<p>I am a graduate student in <a href="http://web.mit.edu/physics/">the Physics Department</a> and <a href="http://space.mit.edu/">Kavli Institute</a> at Massachusetts Institute of Technology. This is my personal website about the my research and my interests.</p>

<p>For research, I am studying galaxy clusters, often called the largest and most massive gravitationally bound objects in the universe. My main project for the PhD thesis is <a href="research.md">the Cluster Hiding in Plain Sight (CHiPS) Survey</a>, which has a goal to find and quantify galaxy clusters hosting extreme central galaxies (starbursts and/or quasars).</p>

